The Delta State Police Command’s Crack Squad has arrested a suspected drug dealer, Solomon Okodaso, as well as the Chairman of Ugbomoro Community in Uvwie Local Government Area, for similar offence. The suspects were arrested during a raid of criminal hideouts in Atata quarters, Ugbomoro community by the police. The police also recovered 12 bottles of codeine, 14 sachets of tramadol, one and half compressed sack of loud, 73 wraps of weeds suspected to be SK, 65, tablets of happy mood drugs, one pack of Colorado, one pack of Arizona, nine packets of razlers, N192,000.00 cash, one Samsung handset, one Infinix handset, one ash-colored Mercedes Benz C350 with reg no. KUJ 664 BH and one white colored Lexus 330 vehicle with reg no. EFR 303 DC from the suspects. The Delta State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe, confirmed the report in a statement signed and made available to DAILY POST. He said, “Investigation is ongoing.”